{"title":"Macworld Podcast: Your hot takes on big iMacs, iOS 17 features, Apple GPT, and more","link":"https://www.macworld.com/article/2006479/hot-takes-big-imacs-ios-17-features-apple-gpt.html","date":1690443000000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.macworld.com\">Macworld</a></p>\n\n<div>\n<section><div></div></section>\n\n\n\n<p>On this episode of the Macworld Podcast, itâ€™s all about your hot takes! You have thoughts on the latest happenings in the world of Apple! Letâ€™s hear what you have to say!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>This is episode 850 with <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/author/Jason-Cross/\" target=\"_blank\">Jason Cross</a>, <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/author/Michael-Simon/\" target=\"_blank\">Michael Simon</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/author/Roman-Loyola/\" target=\"_blank\">Roman Loyola</a>.Â </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Listen to episode 850 on Apple Podcasts</h2>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<h2>Listen to episode 850 on Spotify</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><div>\n\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This episode is all about Macworld reader and listener hot takes. You have thoughts and weâ€™re going to share and respond to what you wrote. All of the comments mentioned in the show can are listed below.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>To beta or not to betaÂ </h2>\n\n\n\n<p>As most of you all know, Apple releases betas or its operating systems, and Apple has a public beta program that users can join if they want to try out the new software. Jason Snell recently wrote a column <a href=\"https://www.macworld.com/article/2000748/why-you-should-install-apple-public-betas.html\">encouraging users to install the betas on their iPhone, iPads, and Macs</a>, reasoning that you can help Apple make better software.  However, not everyone agrees with him.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><div>\n<blockquote><p>Have you all fully lost your minds?</p>â€” Jordan (@tlg_jordan) <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com/?id=111346X1569486&amp;url=https://twitter.com/tlg_jordan/status/1682223259524251648?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&amp;